      <p>When the leash is clipped to the collar, here are the <strong>rules for the dog</strong>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>It's your job to <strong>watch your human's position,</strong> not the other way around.</li>
        <li>While walking, your <strong>butt can't pass the human's leg</strong>.</li>
        <li>Whether walking or at a stand still, <strong>you can not lean into the leash&hellip; ever</strong>. Doing so will never get you where you want to go. It will always be met with a pop.</li>
